      "text": "Once upon a time, in a small village by the sea, there lived an old fisherman who had spent forty years casting his nets into the deep blue. Every morning before dawn, he would push his weathered boat out into the waves, guided only by the stars and the rhythm of the tide. One stormy night, his net caught something heavy\u2014not a fish, but an ancient, rusted chest tied to some seaweed. When he pried it open, it wasn't filled with gold, but with hundreds of sealed glass jars. Each jar contained a different memory: the smell of rain on dry earth, the sound of a child\u2019s laughter, and the warmth of a first kiss. He realized that the most precious treasures aren't always made of gold; some are kept in glass and moments. From then on, he shared one jar each day with the villagers, bringing a little piece of forgotten joy back into their lives.",
